title: How to FIND Your ART STYLE!! 👀🎨 #arttutorial
How to style like Yazhini ❤️🥻 | Cream Kasavu Saree with Brown Short Sleeve Blouse
description:
If you want to achieve that graceful Kerala Kasavu saree look, here’s how to do it.

Start with a classic off-white or cream Kasavu saree—the one with a silver or gold border. It’s simple, elegant, and instantly gives you that traditional Kerala vibe.

Now, pair it with a contrasting blouse—brown, maroon, or any earthy tone works beautifully. Go for a well-fitted, short or elbow-sleeve blouse, and if it has a gold-trimmed edge, even better! It adds that nice mix of tradition and a modern touch.

For accessories, keep it classy. A chunky oxidized silver necklace or a pathakam-style pendant looks stunning with this look. Add a pair of medium-sized jhumkas, and that’s really all you need.

You can skip the bangles or just wear one on each hand to keep things simple and elegant.

For makeup, less is more. Go for skin tones, a small black bindi, and soft kajal-lined eyes. It keeps the look fresh and authentic.

As for hair, leave it open in natural waves or go for a neat braid—both look equally beautiful and suit the minimalist Kerala style.

This look is perfect for Onam, Vishu, or temple visits, giving you that festive yet subtle South Indian charm—traditional, elegant, and timeless.


#yazhini #fashion #saree #howto

title: How to style like Yazhini ❤️🥻 | Printed golden-yellow Saree with Same Sleeveless Blouse
description:
If you want to recreate this trendy boho-ethnic yellow saree look, here’s how you can do it.

Start with a lightweight saree in mustard or golden-yellow tones. Look for something hand-block printed or digitally printed with small geometric or floral patterns—that’s what gives it that artsy, bohemian vibe.

Pair it with a matching or slightly contrasting block-print blouse. Keeping it in the same print family ties the whole outfit together beautifully, making it look chic and effortless.

Saree and Blouse Selection
Go for breathable fabrics like cotton, mulmul, or chiffon—perfect for daywear or warm weather.

If you can, find one with all-over block prints or Kalamkari-style motifs.

For the blouse, you can match the print or play with a subtle contrast using similar shades. Keep the design simple—a sleeveless, cap-sleeve, or boat-neck blouse always looks smart and modern.

Accessories and Styling
Now for the fun part—accessories!
Add oxidized silver jewelry to bring out that boho charm. Think big jhumkas, layered necklaces, or chunky bangles.

Carry a printed sling bag or a handmade tote to keep the artsy feel going.
Leave your hair open in soft waves, or go for a messy bun for that effortless vibe.

Keep your makeup light and natural—just a soft lip, some kajal, and a small bindi to complete the look.

This style is perfect for everyday wear, college, casual outings, travel, or even small festive events. It’s relaxed, comfortable, and still looks super fashionable—just the right mix of ethnic and modern.

#yazhini #fashion #saree #howto
